            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-18T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-18T12:00:00-05:00" n="548" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.6176/4–1045: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-18T13:00:00-04:00">April 18, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>991. ReEmbs 1112, April 10. Department, RDC<note n="73" xml:id="d548fn73">Rubber
                        Development Corporation.</note> and other interested agencies are now
                    considering in detail possible arrangements for the inclusion of Argentina
                    within the control and quota system covering rubber products, rubber substitutes
                    and rubber. Please assure the Foreign Minister<note n="74" xml:id="d548fn74">Macedo Soares, Acting Minister for Foreign Affairs.</note> that we are
                    giving prompt and earnest attention to this problem, that we believe that an
                    overall solution to the numerous questions involved, even if it may require a 2-
                    or 3-week delay, is more desirable than an immediate partial solution, and that
                    we firmly intend to discuss in advance with Brazil any procedure suggested
                    before discussions are initiated with Argentina, to the end that such procedure
                    may be correlated with quota and control plans now in existence.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
